SOURCELONG:Unearthed Arcana - Realm Subclasses	SOURCESHORT:UA	SOURCEWEB:https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/dnd/ua	SOURCEDATE:2024-01																													
																																
###Block: Bard subclass																																
College of the Moon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.Bard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The College of the Moon traces its origins to the ancient druidic circles of the Moonshae Isles, who entrusted the first Bards of this tradition with chronicling the stories of the islands and their people. Bards of this college draw from the islesĺ Fey magic and the primal power of the moonwells to bolster their allies, protect the natural world, and inspire their bardic works. Such works tend to be based on well-known Moonshae myths such as the whimsy of fairy pranksters, the viciousness of the Beast, and the mysteries of the moonwells.	KEY:Bard Subclass ~ College of the Moon																		ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Moonshae Folktales|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Primal Lorist|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,3	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Blessing of the Moonwells|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,6	ABILITY:Bard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|College of the Moon ~ Bolstered Folktales|PREVAREQ:BardLVL,14					SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Moonshae Folktales	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	"DESC:As a Magic action, you can invoke the power of a folktale, imbuing yourself with primal magic until you use this feature again. When you use this feature, choose which of the following folktales you invoke; your choice gives you certain benefits while this magic is active. &nl; Tale of Life. You invoke a tale of vitality and thriving earth. When you restore Hit Points to a creature with a spell, you can expend a Bardic Inspiration die and increase the amount of Hit Points restored by a number equal to a roll of the Bardic Inspiration die. You can do this only once per turn. &nl; Tale of Gloam. You invoke a tale of mystery and secrets. When you use a Bonus Action to give a creature a Bardic Inspiration die, you can take the Disengage or Hide action as part of that Bonus Action. &nl; Tale of Mirth. You invoke a tale of merriment and fey guile. When an enemy you can see within 60 feet of yourself succeeds on a saving throw, you can take a Reaction to expend a Bardic Inspiration die. The creature then must roll the Bardic Inspiration die ansubtract the number rolled from the saveĺs total, possibly causing the save to fail."	KEY:College of the Moon ~Moonshae Folktales																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Primal Lorist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn Druidic and one cantrip from the Druid spell list. It counts as a Bard spell for you but doesnĺt count against the number of cantrips you know. Additionally, choose one of the following skills: Animal Handling, Insight, Medicine, Nature, Perception, or Survival. You have proficiency in that skill.	KEY:College of the Moon ~Primal Lore		DEFINE:DruidicLanguage|1				BONUS:VAR|DruidicLanguage|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bard_Druidic_Cantrip|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bard_Primal_Lorist_Skill|3					ABILITY:Language|AUTOMATIC|Language ~ Druidic													SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Blessing of the Moonwell	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have the Moonbeam spell prepared. As a Bonus Action, you can cast Moonbeam without expending a spell slot. When you cast it using this feature, you glow faintly while you maintain Concentration on the spell. While glowing, you shed Dim Light out to 5 feet, and whenever a creature fails its saving throw against the effects of this Moonbeam, another creature of your choice that you can see within 60 feet of you regains 2d4 Hit Points. Once you use this feature, you canĺt use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 3+ spell slot (no action required).	KEY:College of the Moon ~Blessing of the Moonwell													SPELLS:Blessing of the Moonwell|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=BardLVL|Moonbeam													SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bolstered Folktales	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.College of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The power of your Moonshae Folktales improves. When you use your Tale of Life or Tale of Mirth, you can roll 1d6 and use the number rolled in place of expending a Bardic Inspiration die, and when you use your Tale of Gloam, you can also teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see as part of that Bonus Action.	KEY:College of the Moon ~Bolstered Folktales																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e5d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
### Primal Lorist Cantrips																																
Druidcraft	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		"DESC:Whispering to the spirits of nature, you create one of the following effects within range:&nl;- You create a tiny, harmless sensory effect that predicts what the weather will be at your location for the next 24 hours. The effect might manifest as a golden orb for clear skies, a cloud for rain, falling snowflakes for snow, and so on. This effect persists for 1 round.&nl;- You instantly make a flower blossom, a seed pod open, or a leaf bud bloom.&nl;- You create an instantaneous, harmless sensor effect, such as falling leaves, a puff of wind, the sound of a small animal, or the faint odor of skunk. The effect must fit in a 5-foot cube.&nl;- You instantly light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire."	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Druidcraft																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Druidcraft,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Druidcraft								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elementalism	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip			KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Elementalism																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Elementalism,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Elementalism								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Guidance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one ability check of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the ability check. The spell then ends.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Guidance																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Guidance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Guidance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mending	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Mending																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Mending								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Message	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You point your finger toward a creature within range and whisper a message. The target (and only the target) hears the message and can reply in a whisper that only you can hear. You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know it is beyond the barrier. Magical silence. 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell. The spell doesn't have to follow a straight line and can travel freely around corners or through openings.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Message																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Message,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Message								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Poison Spray	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Poison Spray																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Poison Spray								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Produce Flame	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		"DESC:A flicking flame appears in our hand. The flame remains there for the duration and harms neither you nor your equipment. The flame sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. The spell ends if you dismiss it as an action or if you cast it again.&nl;You can also attack with the flame, although doing so ends the spell. When you cast this spell, or as an action on a later turn, you can hurl the flame at a creature within 30 feet of you. Make a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 fire damage.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8)."	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Produce Flame																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Produce Flame,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Produce Flame								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Resistance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one saving throw of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the saving throw. The spell then ends.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Resistance																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Resistance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Resistance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shillelagh	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:The wood of a club or quarterstaff you are holding is imbued with nature's power. For the duration, you can use your spellcasting ability instead of Streangth for the attack and damage rolls of melee attacks using that weapon, and the weapon's damage die becomes a d8. The weapon also becomes magical, if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of the weapon.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Shillelagh																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Shillelagh,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Shillelagh								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spare the Dying	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		DESC:You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Spare the Dying																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Spare the Dying,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Spare the Dying								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Starry Wisp	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip			KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Starry Wisp																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Starry Wisp,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Starry Wisp								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thunderclap	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip			KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Thunderclap																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclap,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Thunderclap								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thorn Whip	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Bard Druidic Cantrip		"DESC:You create a long, vine-like whip covered in thorns that lashes out at your command toward a creature in range. Make a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the creature takes 1d6 piercing damage, and if the creature is Large or smaller, you pull the creature up to 10 feet closer to you.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th elvel (3d6), and 17th level (4d6)."	KEY:Primal Lorist ~ Thorn Whip																		SPELLS:Primal Lorist|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thorn Whip,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Bard=0|Thorn Whip								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block: Cleric Subclass																																
Knowledge Domain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Cleric Subclass.SpecialQuality.Divine Domain	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Knowledge Domain values learning and understanding above all. Clerics who tap into this domain study esoteric lore, collect old tomes, delve into the secret places of the earth, and examine the process of the mind itself. Gods of knowledge vary from masters of arcane magic to patrons of craft and invention. To them, knowledge is more valuable than material wealth, and the desire to learn is an act of worship. Libraries, universities, and other institutions dedicated to education also draw on the power of the Knowledge Domain. On Faerűn, Clerics of the Knowledge Domain worship deities of learning and ingenuity like Oghma and Gond. Other powerful deitiesŚsuch as Asmodeus, Mystra, Savras, and JergalŚalso count Clerics of the Knowledge Domain among their devotees, as do less-common divinities like Deneir, the Scribe of Oghma, and Azuth, servant of Mystra.	KEY:Cleric Subclass ~ Knowledge Domain																		ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Blessing of Knowledge|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,3	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Knowledge Domain Spells|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,3	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Mind Magic|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,3	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Unfettered Mind|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,6	ABILITY:Cleric Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Knowledge Domain ~ Divine Foreknowledge|PREVAREQ:ClericLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Blessing of Knowledge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality		DESC:You gain proficiency with one type of Artisanĺs Tools of your choice and in two of the following skills of your choice: Arcana, History, Nature, or Religion. You have Expertise in those two skills.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Blessing of Knowledge						BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Artisan's Tools Proficiency|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|2																			SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Knowledge Domain Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Cleric level specified in the Knowledge Domain Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Knowledge Domain Spells														SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Command|Comprehend Languages|Detect Magic|Detect Thoughts|Identify|Mind Spike|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,3	SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Dispel Magic|Nondetection|Tongues|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,5	SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Arcane Eye|Banishment|Confusion|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,7	SPELLS:Knowledge Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=ClericLVL|Legend Lore|Scrying|Synaptic Static|PREVARGTEQ:ClericLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mind Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to manifest your magical knowledge. Choose one spell from the Knowledge Domain Spells table that you have prepared. As part of that action, you cast that spell without expending a spell slot or needing Material components.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Mind Magic																										SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Unfettered Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain telepathy out to 60 feet. When you use this telepathy, you can simultaneously contact a number of creatures equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of one). Additionally, if your total for an Intelligence check is lower than your Wisdom score, you can use that score in place of the total.	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Unfettered Mind						BONUS:VAR|TelepathyRage|60																				SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Divine Foreknowledge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Cleric Class Feature.Class Feature.Knowledge Domain.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you magically expand your mind to the possibilities of the future. For 1 hour, you have Advantage on D20 Tests. Once you use this feature, you canĺt use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of this feature by expending a level 6+ spell slot (no action required).	KEY:Knowledge Domain ~ Divine Foreknowledge																										SORTKEY:Class_Cleric_01d5e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block Figther Subclass																																
Purple Dragon Knight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Fighter Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Purple Dragon Knights are paragons of valor and leadership who partner with amethyst dragons. Such knights aspire to protect the innocent and rally fellow adventurers to the causes of justice and freedom. Although the Purple Dragons were originally founded in Cormyr, new recruits are enlisted from any realms where chivalry is in abundance, including the Silver Marches, Damara, and Chessenta. Characters with this subclass are special among the order. Unlike most Purple Dragons, who partner with amethyst dragons whoĺve already reached adulthood, a Purple Dragon Knight character psionically bonds with an amethyst dragon hatchling. This bond irrevocably transforms both dragon and knight, allowing the dragon to grow in strength alongside its partner knight.	KEY:Fighter Subclass ~ Purple Dragon Knight																		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Knightly Envoy|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Purple Dragon companion|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Dragon Raider|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,7	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Rallying Surge|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,10	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Amethyst Pinnacle|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,15	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Knight ~ Enduring Commander|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Knightly Envoy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn one language of your choice, which you choose from the language tables in the Playerĺs Handbook. Additionally, you can cast the Comprehend Languages spell but only as a Ritual. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for it.	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Knightly Envoy						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Language|1							SPELLS:Kniglthy Envoy|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=FighterLVL|Comprehend Language ~ Ritual,SpellDC_INT													SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Purple Dragon Companion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Purple Dragon Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	"DESC:You are bonded with an amethyst dragon hatchling that serves as your purple dragon companion and uses the Purple Dragon Companion stat block. The purple dragon is Friendly to you and your allies and obeys your commands. &nl; The Dragon in Combat. In combat, the dragon acts during your turn. It can move and use its Reaction on its own, but the only action it takes is the Dodge action unless you take a Bonus Action to command it to take an action in its stat block or some other action. If you have the Incapacitated condition, the dragon acts on its own and isnĺt limited to the Dodge action. &nl; Resurrecting the Dragon. If the dragon companion has died within the last hour, you can take a Magic action to touch the dragon and expend a use of your Second Wind. The dragon returns to life after 1 minute with all its Hit Points restored. Otherwise, you can perform a 1-hour ceremony to resurrect the dragon; this ceremony can be performed as part of a Short or Long Rest."	KEY:Purple Dragon Knight ~ Purple Dragon Companion						BONUS:VAR|PurpleDragonCompanionLVL|FighterLVL							ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Purple Dragon Companion													SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
